headline.main: PIONEER IN AUTOS; Leader in Production Founded Vast Empire in Motors in 1903 HE HAD RETIRED IN 1945 Began Company With Capital of $28,000 Invested by His Friends and Neighbors Henry Ford Is Dead; Founder of Vast Automotive Empire and Leader in Mass Production

abstract: H Ford's contribution to development revd
snippet: DETROIT, April 7 -- Henry Ford, noted automotive pioneer, died at 11:40 tonight at the age of 83. He had retired a little more than a year and a half ago from active direction of the great industrial empire he founded in 1903.
